what makes hardwood floors shine the best without leaving a wax build up wood floor maintenance most wood floors can be kept clean by first sweeping or vacuuming with a floor nozzle to remove most of the surface dust and dirt then damp mopping with clear water dip a sponge in clear water squeezing it out so that the mop is barely damp almost dry use very little water and rinse your mop thoroughly after each use since excess water can dissolve protective coatings alter the color of the wood and raise the grain to roughen the surface if your floors are not dirty enough to need mopping every week then you should not do it as it will wear the floors faster not to mention waste your time simply sweeping is often all they need if need to restore the shine to your wood floor after you get it clean try damp mopping it with cup vinegar and tablespoons furniture polish in a gallon of warm water vinegar is also useful for removing any soap residue or build up but should not be necessary every week Vinegar Vacuum cleaner Upholstery Casting Car washing techniques Menstrual cup Soap Gilding Dry cleaning Brewery Manicure Dairy Lighting Wok Wood Coffee Drill bit Textile manufacturing Fire extinguisher Dishwashing Soap bubble Motor oil Violin Hard water Diseases of the honeybee Soldering Nuclear fallout Dundas Square Plastic Printmaking Printed circuit board Thermal power station Mattress Tattoo Carburetor Sulfuric acid Hemp Seismic retrofit Naval mine Laser printer Pottery Paint Sewage treatment Pebble bed reactor Hamster Hard disk Bong Leather Primer (paint) Sento Compost Hat Opportunity rover Houseplant E85 Dialysis Brazing Etching Fossil fuel power plant Plaster Lacquer Ice resurfacer Japanese toilet Tea Japanese tea ceremony Deforestation Vacuum Biodiesel Oscilloscope Otitis externa Fire fighting Siphon Basement Carpet Cast iron Flax Clothing Fallout shelter Phosphoric acid Concrete Tobacco Straw-bale construction Sterling silver Laser engraving Road Caving Home repair Aerial (